MuscularAtrophyAssert created on 23/Jun/2016 14:21 BHeale

MuscularAtrophyAssert is an assertion model that asserts the presence of Muscular Atrophy.  By definition is the wasting or loss of muscle tissue.

The qualifier body location precoord allows for specifying the body location of the muscular atrophy (such as left arm, calf, etc...).
The qualifier 'associated sign and symptom' allows for specifying a disease state such as ‘diabetes mellitus’ which is associated with the Muscular Atrophy.

This model is intended for the Assertion that muscle atrophy is present and allows for post-coordination of a body location and/or associated condition.
